SIMPLE: ruthenium
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ruthenium
<hw>Ru*the"ni*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So named
from the <etsep>Ruthenians</etsep>, a Little Russian people, as coming
from Russia, the metal having been found in the Ural mountains.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare element of the light platinum group,
found associated with platinum ores, and isolated as a hard, brittle
steel-gray metal which is very infusible. Symbol Ru. Atomic weight
103.5. Specific gravity 12.26. See <cref>Platinum metals</cref>, under
<er>Platinum</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruthful</ent>⟦br⟧
